Quickstrike:




Quickstrike didn't like waking up to a new surroundings where he was 
once in a comfortable setting. He never got to settle down. He was 
careful when he stood. He didn't feel quite himself. Within a few 
steps to test his legs, he closed his optics. He felt dizzy. He 
grabbed his head and took a few more steps ahead. He opened his eyes 
to take a quick look around. 

He walked to off to find a place to lay down before he fell. He found 
a spot by a rock by the wall. He layed down, trying to get out of the 
way of the others, getting a quiet spot. He was drained of energy 
from his body working over time to save him from death. He closed his 
eyes. By the time he woke up, he hoped he would be in better 
conditions.
